TY  - JOUR
TI  - Auctions with Limited Commitment
AU  - Liu, Qingmin
AU  - Mierendorff, Konrad
AU  - Shi, Xianwen
AU  - Zhong, Weijie
AB  - [We study the role of limited commitment in a standard auction environment. In each period, the seller can commit to an auction with a reserve price but not to future reserve prices. We characterize the set of equilibrium profits attainable for the seller as the period length vanishes. An immediate sale by efficient auction is optimal when there are at least three buyers. For many natural distributions two buyers is enough. Otherwise, we give conditions under which the maximal profit is attained through continuously declining reserve prices.]
